-linear arguments and by the non-linear behavior of the MRI in a\nnon-relativistic setting). Under this circumstance, baryon-poor flux in\nhorizontal field domains will be subject to radial buoyancy and to the Parker\ninstability, thereby promoting the growth of poloidal field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 Mar 2002 23:38:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Nov 2003 20:57:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
